      "description": "Offering an exceptional 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in museum-quality condition. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that pulls cleanly to an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec M-variable differential lock, providing unparalleled mechanical feedback. The chassis is structurally immaculate, with a documented inspection confirming zero subframe fatigue or stress fractures. Every suspension component, from the control arm bushings to the dampers, maintains factory-new compliance. This vehicle represents a rare opportunity to acquire a pinnacle of M-division engineering in its most tactile and pristine form.",
